alterations is developed. When applied to special families, this recovers\nthe combinatorics of Weyl groups and double Weyl groups previously used in the\nconstruction and categorification of cluster algebras. It is expected that this\ncombinatorial model of sequences of homogeneous prime elements will have\napplications to the unified categorification of quantum nilpotent algebras.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Sep 2013 15:01:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 May 2015 06:50:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
